<head>
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
    <!-- <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="application.css"> -->
</head>
<html>
   <div class="roundcorners">
        <h1 class="title">PAX NATIONATICA</h1>
        <h3 class="historic">Nations Rising and Falling Every Day</h3>
        <h3 class="main">About</h3>
        <h4>Golden ages. Every region of the world, and virtually every nation of people has experienced one or more.
            A country that might be considered a "failed state" today most likely has a long and rich history of building expansive empires and
            glorious contributions to world art and culture. And just as likely that golden age ended to signal the rise of a new power, thus
            causing the cycle to start anew. It is good sometimes, to look to the past to see that all power is fleeting, and that the backwaters
            of one year have been, and might become again, the 800 pound gorilla of another.
        </h4>
        <br>
        <h4>Select a Region and/or a Time Period</h4>
        <form action="/search" method="post">
            <input type="hidden" name="authenticity_token" value="<%= form_authenticity_token %>">
            <select name="continent_search">
                <%= @nations.each do |nation| %>
                    <option value="<%= nation.continent %>"><%= nation.continent %></option>
                <% end %>
            </select>
            <select name="timeperiod_search">
                <%= @nations.each do |nation| %>
                    <option value="<%= nation.timeperiod %>"><%= nation.timeperiod %></option>
                <% end %>
            </select>
            <input type="submit" value="Submit">
        </form>
        <br>
        <h4>OR search from the current master list of nations....</h4>
        <% @nations.each do |nation| %>
            <!-- <h4 class="nations"><%= nation.nation_name %></h4> -->
            <!-- <p><%= nation.empire %></p> -->
            <h4><li><a href="/<%= nation.nation_name %>"><%= nation.nation_name %></a></li></h4>
        <% end %>
        <br>
        <br>
        <!-- <ul>
            <li><a href="/bhutan">Bhutan</a></li>
            <li><a href="/italy">Italy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/peru">Peru</a></li>
            <li><a href="/phillipines">Phillipines</a></li>
            <li><a href="/sudan">Sudan</a></li>
            <li><a href="/usa">The United States</a></li>
        </ul> -->
    </div>
    <h3 class="main">Welcome: <strong><%= @user.email %></strong></h3>

    <div>
        <h3 class="main">Comments</h3>
        <form action="/messages" method="post">
            <input type="hidden" name="authenticity_token" value="<%= form_authenticity_token %>">
            <textarea name="message[message]" class="message" cols="65" rows="3"></textarea>
            <br>
            <input type="submit" value="Post a Message">
        </form>

        <% @messages.each do |message| %>
            <hr>
            <h4 class="main"><%= "#{message.user.email} - #{message.created_at.strftime("%B #{message.created_at.day.ordinalize}, %Y")}" %></h4>
        	<p class="sub"><%= message.message %></p>
        <% end %>
   </div>
   <br>
   <form action="/logout" method="post">
       <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default">Log Out</button>
   </form>
   <br>
   <br>
</html>
